# Transfusion clinical readiness

Blood transfusion education is **premium adaptive safety and judgment training** integrated across NurseNest — **not** an isolated checklist app, shallow exam sheet, or generic CE module.

## Teach (across lessons, labs correlations, scenarios, cases)

- Safety, monitoring, reaction recognition, prioritization, emergency response, pathophysiology, judgment, escalation, communication, documentation, NGN-style reasoning.

## Integrate (reuse shells, nav, tokens — see ecosystem guardrails)

- **Labs:** Hgb/Hct, iron studies, platelets, coagulation, hemolysis, DIC, sepsis, inflammatory markers — indications, trends, thresholds, clinical significance.  
- **ECG / telemetry:** Deterioration, shock, vitals/dysrhythmia during reactions.  
- **OSCE:** Consent, education, escalation, rapid response communication.  
- **Branching cases:** Evolving reactions, delayed recognition, multiple outcomes (`adaptive-case-study-ecosystem.md`).  
- **Med / infusion:** Timing, compatibility, rates, emergency meds, verification.  
- **Dashboard / adaptive:** Mastery and remediation via **existing** recommendation architecture — no parallel transfusion-only scoring product.

## Tier scaling

RN full workflow + NGN readiness; PN/RPN bedside monitoring and escalation; NP advanced management; New Grad specialty/unit readiness — **pathway/content**, not separate `/app` trees.

